{
  "texts": [
    "I then introduce a potential solution-using large language models (LLMs) such as GPT-4 to augment the creation of psycholinguistic norms.",
    "It is both time-consuming and costly to collect these norms at scale.",
    "As a consequence, older datasets have been relatively small (e.g., fewer than 1000 words).",
    "Within recent decades, the development of online crowd-sourcing tools like Amazon Mechanical Turk foot_1 has enabled larger-scale datasets containing judgments for thousands of words (Winter et al., 2023; Brysbaert et al., 2014a, b).",
    "However, creating these datasets remains a non-trivial task: if the goal is to collect ten judgments each for 40,000 words, a researcher must collect a total of 400,000 judgments."
  ]
}